<@U20T0R475> I have to AWS.  I used the docker images to do so.

<@U20T0R475> It was reasonably easy to do so.  If you want it available outside of AWS you need to do some config / black magic, for example tell it what it’s public hostname/ip is, but if you just want it on a VPC on AWS then it’s fairly straight forward.
